OL,4,Cjumps by a third in a year
OL,6,FEarlier in April, Treasury Committee
OL,7,Fmember Dame Angela Eagle told a
OL,8,Fhearing into insurance: "My
OL,9,Fconstituents and many people who write
OL,10,Fto the committee feel that insurance
OL,11,Fis becoming more of a rip-off.
OL,13,F"Because the price is going up, it's
OL,14,Fharder to make a claim; people, when
OL,15,Fthey do make a claim, often have to
OL,16,Fwait a very long time or aren't dealt
OL,17,Fwith very fairly.
OL,19,F"And that's particularly the case for
OL,20,Finsurance that's compulsory, such as
OL,21,Fdriving insurance."
